  • Possession of THC (2nd+ Offense), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).
  • Carry Concealed Weapon, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.23(2).

records.addlTxt:
15A 022965
Applied bond incorrectly. Had money moved and applied a second time.

Sentencing proceeds.  Statements by counsel and defendant.  

COURT ADVISES the defendant he cannot possess firearms, he must provide a DNA sample and cannot vote until his civil rights are restored.  

Count 1: COURT ORDERS defendant to serve 6 months at the House of Correction - straight time - consecutive to Count 2.  COURT STAYS the sentence and places the defendant on probation for a period of 18  months consecutive to Count 2.

CONDITIONS:  1) no violations of the criminal law rising to the level of probable cause; 2) pay a fine of $500 plus mandatory costs, assessments and surcharges - bail to apply - or a civil judgment is to be entered against the defendant; 3) do not use or possess illegally controlled substances; 4) random screening; 5) AODA, treatment or program; 6) be enrolled in school or seek and maintain employment; 7) cognitive intervention program. 

Count 2: COURT ORDERS defendant to serve 90 days at the House of Correction with Huber for actual work and school and 3 days credit; pay mandatory costs, assessments and surcharges by 8-1-16 or a civil judgment is to be entered against the defendant and subject to other collection.

COURT ORDERS:
- defendant to provide a DNA sample;
- bail to apply to fine and costs.
